C%20Ohio%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63cea2f0fcc41d0018a3a9a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221239%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EYuanshuai%20Si%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERents%20skyrocketed%20after%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20they're%20not%20showing%20any%20signs%20of%20slowing%20down.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20consumers%20are%20either%20moving%20to%20different%20states%20or%20downgrading%20their%20apartments%20to%20save%20money.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBank%20of%20America%20shares%20the%20top%20eight%20cities%20people%20are%20moving%20to%20for%20cheaper%20rent.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20one%20of%20your%20biggest%20monthly%20expenses%2C%20and%20it's%20only%20increasing%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20Redfin%20report%20found%20that%20the%20median%20rent%20in%20the%20US%20is%20now%20%241%2C634%20%E2%80%94%20up%2020%25%20from%20pre-pandemic%20times.%20Rents%20have%20gone%20up%20significantly%20in%20just%20the%20last%20year%2C%20too.%20According%20to%20Consumer%20Price%20Index%20data%2C%20you're%20paying%20almost%205%25%20more%20to%20rent%20the%20same%20apartment%20compared%20to%20this%20time%20a%20year%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rent%20hikes%20are%20driving%20people%20to%20move%20to%20cheaper%20areas%2C%20according%20to%20Bank%20of%20America.%20In%20an%20October%2030%20client%20note%2C%20the%20bank%20found%20that%20based%20on%20its%20deposit%20data%2C%20the%20average%20consumer's%20rent%20payment%20increased%203.7%25%20year%20over%20year%20in%20September%202024.%20That%20discrepancy%20between%20Bank%20of%20America's%20data%20and%20the%20official%20rate%20of%20rent%20inflation%20indicates%20that%20people%20are%20moving%20to%20find%20more%20affordable%20rent%20instead%20of%20staying%20put%2C%20the%20bank%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20are%20either%20moving%20away%20from%20high-cost-of-living%20areas%20or%20downgrading%20within%20the%20same%20city%20to%20save%20money.%20Renters%20make%20up%20around%2034%25%20of%20all%20US%20households%20and%20are%20disproportionately%20younger%20and%20lower-income%20consumers%2C%20meaning%20that%20they're%20more%20price-sensitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20a%20new%20trend%20%E2%80%94%20the%20pandemic%20led%20to%20many%20people%20moving%20to%20places%20with%20cheaper%20rent%20as%20remote%20work%20became%20normalized.%20Now%2C%20persistent%20rent%20increases%20are%20pushing%20consumers%20to%20continue%20moving%20in%20search%20of%20lower%20housing%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBank%20of%20America%20analyzed%20the%20number%20of%20address%20changes%20among%20its%20customer%20base%20to%20track%20migration%20trends.%20The%20bank%20found%20that%20areas%20of%20the%20West%20and%20Northeast%20are%20seeing%20an%20especially%20big%20exodus%20of%20consumers%2C%20with%20rental%20inflation%20in%20the%20Northeast%20rising%20the%20fastest.%20New%20York%2C%20Boston%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20San%20Jose%2C%20and%20Los%20Angeles%20are%20seeing%20the%20biggest%20net%20outflows%20of%20residents%20as%20many%20consumers%20are%20being%20priced%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20contrary%2C%20people%20moving%20to%20Southern%20states%20saw%20only%20a%202%25%20increase%20in%20new%20rents%2C%20below%20the%20rate%20of%20inflation.%20The%20Midwest%20was%20also%20a%20popular%20destination%20for%20consumers%20moving%20across%20state%20lines%2C%20as%20rents%20there%20are%20relatively%20low%20compared%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBank%20of%20America%20identified%20eight%20cities%20where%20people%20are%20moving%20to%20for%20cheaper%20rent%20below%20the%20national%20average%2C%20indicated%20by%20a%20net%20positive%20population%20inflow%20in%20Q3%202024.%20Included%20also%20is%20the%20median%20asking%20rent%20for%20September%202024%2C%20provided%20by%20Redfin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECleveland%2C%20OH%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222124%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cleveland%2C%20Ohio.%5C%