dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThough%20her%20parents%20divorced%20when%20she%20was%20young%2C%20Harris%20maintained%20strong%20ties%20to%20both%20her%20Jamaican%20and%20Indian%20roots.%20She%20often%20speaks%20fondly%20of%20her%20summer%20trips%20to%20India%2C%20where%20she%20was%20deeply%20influenced%20by%20her%20maternal%20grandfather%2C%20a%20retired%20civil%20servant%20and%20her%20visits%20to%20her%20grandmother%2C%20who%20advocated%20for%20women's%20rights%20in%20her%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKamala%20Harris%3A%20Family%20and%20Personal%20Life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%202014%2C%20Kamala%20Harris%20married%20Doug%20Emhoff%2C%20a%20lawyer%2C%20making%20him%20the%20first-ever%20Second%20Gentleman%20of%20the%20United%20States%20when%20Harris%20became%20Vice%20President.%20Emhoff's%20two%20children%20from%20his%20previous%20marriage%2C%20Cole%20and%20Ella%2C%20have%20embraced%20Harris%20as%20their%20stepmother%2C%20affectionately%20referring%20to%20her%20as%20%E2%80%9CMomala.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EKamala%20Harris%20also%20has%20a%20younger%20sister%2C%20Maya%20Harris%2C%20who%20is%20a%20public%20policy%20advocate%20and%20lawyer.%20Maya%20played%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20Kamala's%20political%20campaigns.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKamala%20Harris%3A%20Education%20and%20Legal%20Career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EKamala%20Harris%20earned%20her%20undergraduate%20degree%20from%20Howard%20University%2C%20where%20she%20majored%20in%20political%20science%20and%20economics.%20Afterward%2C%20she%20attended%20UC%20Hastings%20College%20of%20the%20Law%2C%20where%20she%20obtained%20her%20Juris%20Doctor%20in%201989.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHer%20legal%20career%20began%20with%20a%20position%20in%20the%20Alameda%20County%20District%20Attorney's%20Office%20as%20a%20prosecutor.%20Here%2C%20she%20focused%20on%20cases%20involving%20violent%20crime%2C%20particularly%20sexual%20assault%20and%20child%20abuse.%20Kamala%20Harris's%20rise%20in%20the%20legal%20world%20was%20swift.%20In%202003%2C%20she%20was%20elected%20as%20the%20District%20Attorney%20of%20San%20Francisco%2C%20making%20her%20the%20first%20woman%20and%20first%20African%20American%20to%20hold%20the%20position.%20During%20her%20tenure%2C%20she%20introduced%20several%20progressive%20reforms%2C%20including%20a%20reentry%20program%20aimed%20at%20reducing%20recidivism%20and%20increasing%20opportunities%20for%20offenders%20to%20reintegrate%20into%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%202011%2C%20Harris%20was%20elected%20as%20California's%20Attorney%20General%2C%20as%20the%20first%20woman%20and%20person%20of%20colour%20to%20hold%20the%20position.%20As%20AG%2C%20Kamala%20Harris%20took%20on%20major%20issues%20like%20environmental%20protection%2C%20consumer%20rights%20and%20marriage%20equality%2C%20while%20also%20contending%20with%20criticism%20over%20her%20stance%20on%20law%20enforcement%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKamala%20Harris%3A%20Political%20Career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EKamala%20Harris's%20political%20ascent%20continued%20when%20she%20was%20elected%20as%20the%20US%20Senator%20from%20California%20in%202016%2C%20succeeding%20Barbara%20Boxer.%20Her%20time%20in%20the%20Senate%20gained%20national%20attention%20when%2C%20during%20high-profile%20hearings%2C%20she%20questioned%20key%20figures%20like%20then-Attorney%20General%20Jeff%20Sessions%20and%20Supreme%20Court%20nominee%20Brett%20Kavanaugh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EDuring%20her%20Senate%20term%2C%20Kamala%20Harris%20worked%20on%20critical%20issues%2C%20including%20immigration%20reform%2C%20healthcare%2C%20criminal%20justice%20reform%20and%20civil%20rights.%20She%20was%20a%20strong%20advocate%20for%20the%20DREAM%20Act%2C%20aimed%20at%20protecting%20young%20immigrants%2C%20and%20also%20co-sponsored%20legislation%20addressing%20the%20opioid%20epidemic%20and%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%202019%2C%20Harris%20launched%20her%20campaign%20for%20the%20Democratic%20presidential%20nomination.%20Although%20her%20campaign%20ended%20before%20the%20primaries%2C%20her%20impact%20on%20the%20political%20stage%20was%20undeniable.%20In%20August%202020%2C%20Harris%20was%20chosen%20by%20Joe%20Biden%20as%20his%20running%20mate%2C%20making%20history%20as%20the%20first%20woman%20of%20South%20Asian%20and%20African%20American%20descent%20to%20be%20nominated%20for%20Vice%20President%20by%20a%20major%20political%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOn%20January%2020%2C%202021%2C%20Kamala%20Harris%20was%20sworn%20in%20as%20the%2049th%20Vice%20President%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20making%20history%20once%20again%20as%20the%20highest-ranking%20female%20official%20in%20US%20history.%20Her%20vice%20presidency%20is%20marked%20by%20her%20leadership%20on%20issues%20such%20as%20economic%20recovery%2C%20voting%20rights%20and%20foreign%20policy%2C%20and%20she%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20key%20figure%20in%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20efforts%20to%20combat%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20and%20rebuild%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFor%20the%202024%20US%20presidential%20election%2C%20Kamala%20Harris%20is%20the%20Democratic%20presidential%20nominee%2C%20with%20Tim%20Walz%20as%20her%20running%20mate.%20They%20are%20going%20head-to-head%20against%20Republican%20candidate%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20his%20running%20mate%2C%20JD%20Vance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKamala%20Harris%3A%20Net%20Worth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EKamala%20Harris's%20net%20worth%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20around%20%248%20million%2C%20combined%20with%20her%20husband%20Douglas%20Emhoff's%20assets%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20follow%2C%20no%20index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fkylemullins%2F2024%2F05%2F26%2Fheres-how-much-kamala-harris-is-worth%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EForbes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20amount%20is%20up%20from%20%247%20million%20in%202021%20and%20is%20roughly%2020%20times%20the%20median%20net%20worth%20of%20Americans%20in%20their%20age%20bracket.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EKamala%20Harris%20has%20also%20authored%20two%20books%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98Smart%20on%20Crime'%2C%20a%20reflection%20of%20her%20criminal%20justice%20philosophy%2C%20and%20%E2%80%98The%20Truths%20We%20Hold'%2C%20a%20memoir%20recounting%20her%20life%20experiences%20and%20political%20journey%20%E2%80%93%20which%20have%20contributed%20to%20her%20financial%20standing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKamala%20Harris%3A%20Honours%20and%20Recognition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThroughout%20her%20career%2C%20Kamala%20Harris%20has%20received%20numerous%20accolades%20for%20her%20contributions%20to%20public%20service%20and%20social%20justice.%20She%20was%20named%20in%20Time%20magazine's%20100%20Most%20Influential%20People%20multiple%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EShe%20has%20been%20honoured%20by%20organisations%20such%20as%20the%20NAACP%20(National%20Association%20for%20the%20Advancement%20of%20Colored%20People)%2C%20political%20action%20committee%20EMILY's%20List%20and%20The%20National%20Women's%20Hall%20of%20Fame%20for%20her%20work%20in%20civil%20rights%2C%20women's%20empowerment%20and%20public%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EKamala%20Harris%20has%20also%20received%20honorary%20doctorates%20from%20institutions%20like%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%20and%20Howard%20University%20in%20recognition%20of%20her%20achievements.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730567760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F