It%20started%20in%20Rome%20and%20eventually%20stretched%20out%20to%20the%20port%20city%20of%20Brindisi.%20Today%2C%20the%20roads%20are%20covered%20because%20of%20the%20urbanization%20of%20Rome.%3Cp%3Eessevu%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20now%20known%20as%20Frattocchie%20was%20connected%20to%20other%20Italian%20cities%20via%20roads%20that%20led%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-things-to-do-in-italy-from-couple-vacation-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAppian%20Way%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20constructed%20starting%20in%20312%20BCE%20and%20is%20considered%20Europe's%20first%20major%20highway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20the%20Appian%20Way%20ran%20for%20132%20miles%20between%20Rome%20and%20Capua%20in%20Campania%2C%20southeast%20of%20Rome.%20Eventually%2C%20it%20was%20extended%20across%20the%20country%20to%20the%20port%20of%20Brindisi%2C%20close%20to%20the%20Adriatic%20Sea.%20Today%2C%20the%20road%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwhc.unesco.org%2Fen%2Flist%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUNESCO%20World%20Heritage%3C%2Fa%3E%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20workers%20constructing%20a%20new%20McDonald's%20discovered%20an%20offshoot%20of%20the%20road%20in%20Frattocchie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBefore%20the%20restaurant%20opened%20in%202017%2C%20McDonald's%20partnered%20with%20archeologists%20to%20restore%20the%20remains%20of%20the%20ancient%20Roman%20road.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221777%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20display%20sign%20which%20showcases%20historical%20facts%20about%20the%20gallery%20underneath%20McDonald's%20in%20Rome.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67238da5a0a0cc14f2253394%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20board%20displaying%20the%20history%20of%20the%20archeological%20findings%20at%20the%20viewing%20gallery%20built%20under%20the%20McDonald's%20in%20Frattocchie.%3Cp%3EGary%20He%2FMcAtlas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20early%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-digital-twin-technology-can-transform-archeological-research-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earcheological%20investigations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Rome's%20Superintendency%20for%20Archaeology%20said%20it%20had%20unearthed%20a%20150-foot-long%20road%20that%20diverged%20from%20the%20Appian%20Way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20section%20of%20the%20road%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20been%20constructed%20between%20the%201st%20and%202nd%20centuries%20BC.%20News%20outlet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelocal.it%2F20170223%2Fmcdonalds-opens-restaurant-museum-over-ancient-roman-road%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Local%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20travelers%20stopped%20using%20it%20three%20centuries%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArcheologists%20discovered%20the%20path%20had%20become%20a%20burial%20site%20and%20contained%20the%20skeletons%20of%20three%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcDonald's%20donated%20300%2C000%20euros%20toward%20the%20three-year%20restoration%2C%20and%20afterward%2C%20the%20road%20was%20incorporated%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthen-and-now-mcdonalds-restaurants-through-the-years%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%20restaurant%20design%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EToday%2C%20visitors%20can%20see%20the%20ancient%20road%20as%20they%20walk%20over%20a%20glass%20floor%20into%20the%20restaurant.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221779%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20ancient%20Roman%20roadway%20gallery%20underneath%20a%20McDonald's.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67238d7a01ea6d83dee5554d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20road%20seen%20here%20is%20made%20up%20of%20local%20volcanic%20rocks.%20The%20strips%20of%20white%20light%20above