t%20share%20the%20science%20(even%20though%20sharing%20everything%20is%20definitely%20the%20right%20strategy%20in%20the%20short%20and%20possibly%20medium%20term%20for%20recruitment%20purposes).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20screenshot%20OpenAI%20published%20showed%20Musk%20responding%20simply%2C%20%26quot%3BYup.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-drops-lawsuit-against-sam-altman-and-openai-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMusk%20dropped%20the%20lawsuit%20in%20June%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-sues-openai-sam-altman-again-why-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiling%20a%20new%20lawsuit%20in%20August%3C%2Fa%3E%20alleging%20he%20was%20%26quot%3B%3Cspan%3Edeceived%26quot%3B%20into%20cofounding%20the%20AI%20firm.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20to%20be%20open-%20or%20closed-source%20is%20a%20hot%20topic%20in%20the%20AI%20industry%20right%20now.%20One%20of%20OpenAI's%20competitors%20that%20touts%20its%20open-source%20efforts%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-open-source-ai-platforms-future-competition-apple-llama-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whose%20latest%20offering%20in%20the%20space%2C%20the%20Llama%203.2%20models%2C%20came%20out%20in%20September.%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20has%20said%20he%20believes%20open-source%20is%20%26quot%3Bsafer%20than%20the%20alternatives%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bnecessary%20for%20a%20positive%20AI%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20worth%20noting%20the%20company%20requires%20firms%20with%20a%20user%20base%20of%20700%20million%20active%20users%20a%20month%20or%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-llama-2-ai-model-not-open-source-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20request%20use%20of%20Llama%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Meta%20can%20decide%20whether%20to%20grant%20access%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nonprofit%20Open%20Source%20Initiative%20has%20previously%20said%20this%20license%20%26quot%3Bwould%20not%20be%20qualified%20as%20an%20open-source%20license%20because%20it%20contains%20restrictions%20on%20commercial%20needs.%26quot%3B%20The%20OSI%20also%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.emarketer.com%2Fcontent%2Fnew-industry-definition-of-open-source-ai-challenges-meta-s-llama-model%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20Meta's%20Llama%20doesn't%20satisfy%20its%20definition%20of%20open-source%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Meta%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20disagrees%20with%20OSI's%20definition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20single%20open%20source%20AI%20definition%2C%20and%20defining%20it%20is%20a%20challenge%20because%20previous%20open%20source%20definitions%20do%20not%20encompass%20the%20complexities%20of%20today's%20rapidly%20advancing%20AI%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20make%20Llama%20free%20and%20openly%20available%2C%20and%20our%20license%20and%20Acceptable%20Use%20Policy%20help%20keep%20people%20safe%20by%20having%20some%20restrictions%20in%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20continue%20working%20with%20OSI%20and%20other%20industry%20groups%20to%20make%20AI%20more%20accessible%20and%20free%20responsibly%2C%20regardless%20of%20technical%20definitions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElsewhere%20in%20the%20Reddit%20AMA%2C%20Altman%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-answer-reddit-ama-questions-openai-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI's%20GPT-5%20model%20is%20likely%20not%20launching%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20that%20he%20was%20using%20ChatGPT%20to%20respond%20to%20some%20of%20the%20online%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2