cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcy9jdpep4ydo.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcy9jdpep4ydo.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20a%20free%20meal%20cost%20an%20investor%20his%20retirement%20savings%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20plate%20with%20cash%20on%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67225a1201ea6d83dee51a28%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20iStock%3B%20Natalie%20Ammari%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGeorge%20Wilson%20learned%20the%20hard%20way%20that%20there's%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20a%20free%20lunch%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20in%20his%20case%2C%20a%20free%20dinner%20that%20cost%20him%20a%20chunk%20of%20his%20retirement%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20retiree%2C%20he%20regularly%20received%20postcards%20in%20the%20mail%2C%20offering%20to%20teach%20him%20about%20finance%20and%20how%20to%20make%20money%20in%20retirement.%20They%20usually%20involved%20a%20presentation%20at%20a%20nice%20restaurant%2C%20and%20he%20would%20go%20without%20acting%20on%20any%20of%20the%20investment%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20on%20one%20occasion%2C%20Wilson%20did%20take%20the%20bait%20after%20a%20brochure%20he%20received%20in%202010%20inviting%20him%20to%20an%20evening%20at%20Ruth's%20Chris%20Steak%20House%20ended%20up%20costing%20him%20%24158%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20very%20good%20restaurant.%20And%20so%2C%20of%20course%2C%20it%20caught%20my%20attention%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilson%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20fateful%20dinner%2C%20he%20enjoyed%20his%20favorite%20top%20sirloin%20steak%2C%20asparagus%20tips%2C%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bfabulous%26quot%3B%20chocolate%20cake.%20He%20also%20met%20David%20Escarcega%2C%20one%20of%20the%20hosts%20and%20a%20broker%20who%20would%20eventually%20advise%20him%20to%20invest%20in%20so-called%20non-correlated%2C%20fixed-income%20alternative%20products%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investmentnews.com%2Falternatives%2Fgwg-holdings-files-for-bankruptcy%2F220355%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enow-bankrupt%20firm%20GWG%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYears%20later%2C%20Wilson%20is%20still%20fighting%20to%20regain%20what%20he%20lost%20from%20that%20investment.%20An%20arbitration%20decision%20recently%20awarded%20him%20%24267%2C252%20in%20compensation%2C%20including%20emotional%20distress%20damages%20from%20the%20last%20broker%20who%20facilitated%20the%20transaction.%20But%20the%20respondent%20only%20paid%20approximately%20%24103%2C363.40%20toward%20sanctions%20and%20the%20award.%20After%20costs%2C%20Mr.%20Wilson%20will%20end%20up%20with%20almost%20no%20payout%2C%20according%20to%20his%20attorney.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFancy%20restaurants%20with%20presentations%20are%20a%20common%20practice%20in%20the%20industry%2C%20says%20financial%20planner%20Michael%20Murray%2C%20adding%20that%20there%20are%20services%20that%20provide%20mailing%20lists%20of%20people%20with%20a%20certain%20net%20worth%2C%20and%20retirees%20are%20often%20on%20them%20because%20it's%20where%20wealth%20tends%20to%20be%20concentrated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20those%20meals%20aren't%20really%20free%2C%20Murray%20said.%20They're%20predominantly%20set%20up%20to%20sell%20high-commission%20products.%20In%20GWG's%20case%2C%20brokers%20earned%20up%20to%208%25%20in%20commissions.%20What%20advisors%20can%20earn%20from%20one%20of%20these%20events%20pays%20for%20the%20meals%20and%20more.%20Picture%20a%20scenario%20where%20an%20advisor%20signs%20up%20%24500%2C000%20worth%20of%20investments%20with%20an%208%25%20commission%20rate%3B%20that's%20a%20%2440%2C000%20payout.%20The%20math%20is%20very%20favorable%20for%20those%20who%20do%20this%20regularly%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20invitees%20feel%20like%20the%20hosts%20have%20done%20something%20nice%20for%20them%20and%20there's%20an%20implication%20that%20they%20should%20do%20something%20back%2C%20Murray%20noted.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20think%20certain%20people%20will%20go%20to%20these%20dinner%20seminars%20and%20almost%20feel%20an%20obligation%20to%20work%20with%20someone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3Bfree%20lunch%20seminars%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Adam%20Gana%2C%20a%20securities%20attorney%20who%20worked%20on%20Wilson's%20case.%20They're%20common%20in%20the%20industry.%20But%20Gana%20says%20that%20when%20brokerage%20firms%20offer%20them%2C%20he%20tells%20clients%20to%20run%20the%20other%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20see%20them%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Gana%20said.%20%26quot%3BI've%20represented%203%2C000%20investors%20over%20the%20last%2015%20years%2C%20and%20in%20so%20many%20of%20those%20instances%20when%20we're%20dealing%20with%20a%20horrific%20product%2C%20a%20non-traded%20product%2C%20a%20product%20that's%20just%20terrible%20for%20investors%2C%20it%20usually%20starts%20with%20a%20free%20lunch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2274285f86-a363-43ff-b132-9ec411f82f14%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERisky%20business%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20dinner%2C%20Wilson%20and%20his%20ex-wife%20Jean%20followed%20up%20with%20Escarcega%20at%20his%20office%20to%20discuss%20alternative%20investment%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20sat%20down%20with%20him%2C%20and%20he%20went%20through%20various%20opportunities%20that%20he%20could%20present%20to%20us%2C%20and%20we%20asked%20for%20several%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilson%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20one%20that%20seemed%20the%20most%20attractive%20and%20that%20he%20extolled%20the%20virtues%20of%20the%20most%20was%20GWG.%20And%20so%20we%20thought%20about%20it%20for%20several%20weeks%20and%20went%20back%20and%20forth%20and%20then%20ultimately%20decided%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20products%20were%20non-publicly%20traded%20so-called%20LifeNotes%2C%20high-yield%20debt%20securities%20that%20paid%20a%209%25%20monthly%20interest%20rate%20by%20GWG%20Holdings%2C%20according%20to%20documents%20viewed%20by%20Insider.%20They%20were%20based%20on%20life%20insurance%20policies%20purchased%20on%20the%20secondary%20market%2C%20with%20the%20expectation%20that%20death%20benefits%20would%20be%20paid%20to%20GWG's%20bondholders%20when%20the%20insured%20died.%20One%20brochure%2C%20viewed%20by%20Insider%2C%20advertised%20them%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsecured%20investment%20backed%20by%20a%20large%20portfolio%20of%20high-quality%20life%20insurance%20policies%26quot%3B%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEscarcega%20had%20pitched%20them%20as%20a%20safer%20alternative%20to%20the%20volatile%20stock%20market%20that%20could%20provide%20steady%20dividend%20payouts%20while%20preserving%20the%20principal%20investments%2C%20Wilson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20we%20want%20to%20leave%20our%20equity%20to%20our%20children%20but%20have%20some%20kind%20of%20income%20coming%20from%20it%20while%20we're%20still%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilson%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20that%20was%20very%20attractive%20to%20us%2C%20that%20we%20preserve%20our%20equity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilson%20initially%20purchased%20%24180%2C000%20worth%20of%20the%20notes%20using%20funds%20from%20his%20IRA%2C%20according%20to%20documents%20viewed%20by%20Insider.%20He%20later%20reduced%20his%20investment%20to%20%24158%2C000%20and%20flipped%20it%20to%20GWG%20preferred%20stock.%20For%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20things%20were%20looking%20good.%20Wilson%20received%20payouts%20monthly.%20In%202017%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20renew%20his%20investment%2C%20according%20to%20documents%20viewed%20by%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20he%20didn't%20know%20was%20that%20by%20then%2C%20Escarcega%20had%20been%20barred%20from%20selling%20securities%20after%20misrepresenting%20investment%20risks%2C%20according%20to%20FINRA.%20So%20Escarcega%20used%20his%20brother%20Adrian's%20license%20to%20submit%20the%20transactions%20through%20AGES%20Financial%20Services%2C%20according%20to%20arbitration%20documents%20from%20Wilson's%20attorneys.%20The%20Escarcegas%20could%20not%20be%20reached%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20one%20of%20many%20details%20Wilson%20wasn't%20aware%20of.%20Thus%20far%2C%20the%20payouts%20had%20always%20been%20timely%2C%20he%20said.%20So%2C%20there%20was%20no%20reason%20to%20suspect%20there%20were%20problems.%20But%20there%20were.%20GWG's%20balance%20sheet%20wasn't%20adding%20up.%20FINRA%20had%20determined%20that%20it%20hadn't%20been%20profitable%20in%20over%20a%20decade.%20The%20firm%20had%20been%20selling%20new%20bonds%20to%20pay%20dividends%20to%20existing%20bondholders.%20The%20underlying%20collateral%20wasn't%20generating%20an%20income%20and%20multiple%20accounting%20firms%20refused%20to%20audit%20it%2C%20according%20to%20the%20amended%20statement%20of%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20doom%20loop%20would%20eventually%20come%20to%20a%20screeching%20halt%20due%20to%20GWG's%20accounting%20issues%2C%20an%20SEC%20investigation%2C%20and%20failure%20to%20file%20its%20annual%20SEC%20report.%20By%202021%2C%20it%20could%20no%20longer%20sell%20bonds%20which%20led%20to%20its%20bankruptcy%20by%202022%20and%20the%20halting%20of%20dividend%20payments%2C%20according%20to%20the%20amended%20statement%20of%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECraig%20McCann%2C%20a%20consultant%20providing%20expert%20testimony%20in%20investment%20cases%2C%20including%20this%20one%2C%20said%20that%20GWG's%20insurance%20contracts%20were%20being%20overvalued%20on%20its%20balance%20sheet%20and%20the%20firm%20was%20assuming%20that%20people%20would%20die%20earlier.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20they%20estimated%20receiving%20the%20death%20benefits%20sooner.%20Simply%20put%2C%20there%20were%20not%20enough%20benefits%20being%20paid%20on%20the%20insurance%20contracts%20to%20cover%20the%20interest%20and%20principal%20due.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20lots%20of%20signals%2C%26quot%3B%20McCann%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20lots%20of%20problems%20with%20their%20SEC%20filings%20and%20lots%20of%20reasons%20to%20believe%20that%20it%20was%20imminently%20going%20to%20happen%2C%20but%20most%20investors%20were%20very%20unsophisticated%20investors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investmentnews.com%2Falternatives%2Fclients-win-another-gwg-bond-claim-this-time-against-b-d%2F245442%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAGES%20had%20ended%20its%20relationship%20with%20GWG%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20a%20change%20in%20the%20company's%20business%20model%2C%20according%20to%20the%20firm.%20But%20Wilson%20says%20he%20was%20not%20informed%20by%20the%20firm%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investmentnews.com%2Ffixed-income%2Finvestors-claiming-emotional-distress-damages-win-lawsuit-involving-gwg-bonds%2F257068%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreventing%20him%20from%20selling%20his%20shares%20in%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%20(AGES%20disputes%20this).%20An%20arbitration%20panel%20found%20that%20the%20investment%20scheme%20was%20so%20egregious%20that%20they%20awarded%20him%20%24267%2C252.00%20in%20compensation%20that%20included%20emotional%20distress%20damages%2C%20according%20to%20the%20order.%20AGES%20paid%20%24103%2C000%20for%20all%20claimants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229e594bc3-8860-404f-8b63-aeb5d0906705%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERisk%20reward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWilson's%20situation%20is%20a%20cautionary%20tale.%20He%20used%20his%20IRA%20to%20make%20the%20investment%2C%20so%20he's%20also%20faced%20with%20a%20required%20minimum%20distribution%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20amount%20invested%20in%20GWG%20even%20though%20it's%20nominal.%20He%20told%20Insider%20he%20must%20withdraw%20from%20other%20investments%20to%20meet%20the%20minimum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20case%20isn't%20an%20isolated%20one.%20There%20may%20have%20been%20thousands%20of%20brokers%20selling%20GWG%20bonds%2C%20based%20on%20data%20pulled%20from%20ADV%20filings%20as%20reported%20by%20McCann.%20Wilson%20says%20he%20lives%20with%20the%20guilt%20of%20advising%20his%20ex-wife%20and%20a%20friend%20who%20also%20invested%20in%20the%20bonds%20and%20lost%20their%20principal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETruth%20be%20told%2C%20it's%20difficult%20for%20the%20average%20retiree%20who%20is%20not%20financially%20savvy%20to%20understand%20the%20mechanics%20of%20many%20of%20these%20alternative%20investments%2C%20even%20when%20there%20are%20red%20flags%2C%20Murray%20said.%20Non-publicly%20traded%20investments%20take%20time%20to%20build%20capital%20before%20generating%20free%20cash%20flow.%20For%20those%20with%20lower%20cash%20reserves%2C%20they%20don't%20make%20much%20sense%20because%20they%20lack%20liquidity%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Murray%20also%20emphasized%20that%20not%20all%20alternative%20investments%20are%20bad.%20He%20just%20thinks%20that%20if%20you're%20considering%20them%2C%20you%20must%20be%20financially%20savvy%20and%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20dig%20into%20offering%20statements%2C%20look%20at%20fee%20structures%2C%20and%20related%20party%20transactions.%20Even%20then%2C%20investors%20should%20resort%20to%20a%20second%20opinion%20from%20a%20fiduciary%20advisor%2C%20a%20CPA%2C%20or%20an%20attorney.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20understand%20that%20risk%20and%20reward%20are%20always%20tied%20together.%20Outsized%20promises%20of%20yields%20that%20are%20much%20higher%20than%2C%20say%2C%20the%2010-Year%20Treasury%20is%20a%20red%20flag%20and%20means%20there's%20elevated%20risk%2C%20Murray%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-a-free-meal-cost-an-investor-his-retirement-savings-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730562541000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67226e439b3250dbbceb2e36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%